This paper focuses on children's understanding of online privacy risks and their coping strategies, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cyber security (cs.CR). The study also involves language use and comprehension, which could be categorized under computational linguistics (cs.CL) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study involves the use of digital technologies, which could be categorized under computer systems and networking (cs.CY).
